name: Gunung Agung
address: Besakih, Bebandem, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80863, Indonesia
review 1: Mount Agung or Gunung Agung is a volcano in Bali, Indonesia, southeast of Mt Baturvolcano, also in Bali. Gunung Agung stratovolcano is the highest point on Bali. It dominates the surrounding area, influencing the climate, especially rainfall patterns. From a distance, the mountain appears to be perfectly conical. From the peak of the mountain, it is possible to see the peak of Mt Rinjani on the nearby island of Lombok, to the east, although both mountains are frequently covered in clouds.
review 2: This temple has a lot of steps down, but you get to a set of ancient tombs, making it quite different from the usual Bali temples.
review 3: One of the Best views in indonesia
review 4: Started besaik at 1130pm for Sunrise didn't manage to complete. Please don't underestimate the mountain. Train hard and wear proper shoes. Be prepared for temp drop as u climb higher.
